sub_title: Researcher PHD Student bij National University of Singapore
summary: Trained as an architectural historian and spatial planner, I specialised on heritage conservation management and urban redevelopment policies and practices in Indonesia. During recent work activities I have gained relevant experience in both sectors of spatial planning and heritage conservation, and have been able to deepen my skills as a researcher by conducting extensive fieldwork and writing academic reports. Through my experience in conducting interdisciplinary research, my abilities to work both independently as in a team, my social and analytical skills, and my international experience, I carry strong potentials to bring in a novel perspective in understanding the socio-political issues in heritage conservation management and transitioning towards a more inclusive and effective urban redevelopment
